Is it necessary to use Chimera for this case ?
I think No. It would be better to have one (single) domain,
to avoid interpolations (computing gradients as the vorticity
is not good at the interfaces when using Chimera) !
Inlet velocity (sinus)
Mesh discussion
• 3D grid : 3 million cells (42 blocks) : very slow in time simulation (dt =
10E-5 sec). Tried to split (MB split) does not work because of the
chimera.
• We can’t go to higher frequencies due to the coarser mesh => high
frequency => small time step =/= coarse mesh.
• We can’t do a parametric analysis using this grid, it takes long time to
converge (15 – 20 days maybe more).
